%h1
  Training and staff development

%p
  %b
    Bridging the gap between mental wellness and performance training.
  
%p
  Mindapples teaches people how to use their minds effectively. We offer bite-size insights from experimental psychology and neuroscience about how our minds work and how to use them, covering essential topics from handling pressure to thinking creatively. Available in full programmes or as bespoke packages, each session is delivered by experienced trainers and packed with practical tools and techniques to increase your resilience and manage yourself and others better. 
  
%p
  Our clients include some of the biggest names in global business, including News UK, L'Oreal, JP Morgan and the Wellcome Trust. Our sessions are getting amazing feedback, with 
  %i
    over 90% of participants rating our sessions as "good" or "excellent" 
  and saying they will change their behaviour as a result of what they have learnt.
 
%p
  %i
    "I certainly found the approach novel and informative which is praise indeed having been to so many "stress management sessions"."
  %b
    Dr David Matthews, MB, BS, DRCOG, DOccMed, AFOM, FRCGP, Occupational Physician

%h2
  A Mind for Business

%h4  
  Developing the mental resources of your business

%p
  Our core programme covers all the key elements of how our minds work. In 1-hour sessions in groups of up to 30 participants, we share insights on motivation, creativity, influence, pressure and more, and work with staff to help them manage their minds successfully. We also offer these sessions as extended 90-minute executive sessions, facilitated by occupational psychologists and delivered in classroom sessions or via telepresence, to help your leaders transform your organisation and reach their mental potential.

